# Single-origin architecture: the production build reads no PUBLIC_* env vars.
# Runtime config (Clerk publishable key, Sentry environment, release SHA) is
# served by the Axum backend at GET /api/config.json and fetched on first load.
#
# This file only affects `npm run dev`. The dev server proxies /api/* to a
# local Rust backend. Override the backend URL if you run it on a non-default
# host/port:
#
# VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3100

# Frontend Sentry. Read at BUILD time by Vite (via $env/dynamic/public in
# hooks.client.ts). Without these, Sentry.init is never called and every
# captureException is a silent no-op — that's how we ran blind from PR #62
# (Vercel retire) until 2026-04-20. For prod, set these in
# `frontend/.env.production` (gitignored), not here.
# PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
# PUBLIC_SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=dev
